title: How to Make Breadsticks Like Olive Garden

steps.headline: Gather the following ingredients to make 12 authentic tasting Olive Garden breadsticks:
Pour warm water into a bowl.
steps.description: Add the sugar and yeast, and let it sit for 5 minutes or until the top becomes foamy.

steps.headline: Combine bread flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Attach the paddle attachment to the stand mixer, and work in the softened butter.
steps.description: If you don't have a stand mixer, use a wooden spoon to mix the butter and flour.

steps.headline: Add the warm water/yeast/sugar mixture to the flour/butter mixture, and use the dough hook to knead for 10 minutes.
steps.description: If you don't have a stand mixer, scrape the dough onto the counter top and knead by hand for 10 minutes.

steps.headline: Put the dough into a covered bowl, and let it rise until it doubles in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Divide the dough into 12 equal pieces by cutting it in half, then cutting each half in half and then each quarter into thirds.
Roll each portion of dough into a stick 7 inches (17.8 cm) long.
Place the rolls on a cookie sheet covered with parchment paper.
steps.description: Cover with a clean cloth or plastic wrap, and set aside until the breadsticks double in size--approximately 1 1/2 hours.

steps.headline: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (204.4 Celsius)
Bake the breadsticks for 12 minutes or until they are golden brown.
Remove the breadsticks from the oven, and quickly brush the top of each one with the melted butter and sprinkle with garlic salt.

"} Pour warm water into a bowl. Add the sugar and yeast, and let it sit for 5 minutes or until the top becomes foamy. Combine bread flour and salt in mixing bowl. Attach the paddle attachment to the stand mixer, and work in the softened butter. If you don't have a stand mixer, use a wooden spoon to mix the butter and flour. Add the warm water/yeast/sugar mixture to the flour/butter mixture, and use the dough hook to knead for 10 minutes. If you don't have a stand mixer, scrape the dough onto the counter top and knead by hand for 10 minutes. Put the dough into a covered bowl, and let it rise until it doubles in size, about 1 1/2 hours. Divide the dough into 12 equal pieces by cutting it in half, then cutting each half in half and then each quarter into thirds. Roll each portion of dough into a stick 7 inches (17.8 cm) long. Place the rolls on a cookie sheet covered with parchment paper. Cover with a clean cloth or plastic wrap, and set aside until the breadsticks double in size--approximately 1 1/2 hours. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (204.4 Celsius) Bake the breadsticks for 12 minutes or until they are golden brown. Remove the breadsticks from the oven, and quickly brush the top of each one with the melted butter and sprinkle with garlic salt.
